The Arduino acts as a **display device** for real-time game stats (e.g., letters per second, username). The game publishes these stats to an MQTT topic (e.g., `game/room123/stats`). The Arduino subscribes to this topic using an MQTT library (e.g., PubSubClient) and updates an LCD screen accordingly. Example Arduino code:
cpp
#include <PubSubClient.h>
PubSubClient client(espClient);
void callback(char* topic, byte* payload, unsigned int length) {
  String msg = String((char*)payload);
  lcd.clear();
  lcd.print("LPS: " + msg); // Display letters per second
}
